wake transitions are clinically critical moments when REM atonia can intrude into wakefulness, forming the basis of sleep paralysis and REM intrusion patterns in narcolepsy. Consumer wearables rely on PPG/actigraphy and cannot reliably detect REM or 
boundaries. Wearable EEG is emerging, but there is no validated REM\endash 
wake transition detection framework for real-world use. This project builds and validates a transition detection algorithm for wearable EEG using public paired PSG + wearable datasets, eval
uates generalization across subjects and datasets, and produces a real-time inference prototype. Closed-loop intervention is a future phase.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f46\cf19\insrsid1127742 
